# Pipeline Script Conventions

## Shell Standards

- Start every script with `#!/bin/bash` and `set -euo pipefail`
- Use `log()` for all output (defined in orchestrator.sh, run-pipeline.sh, and run-agent.sh)
- Quote all variable expansions: `"$var"` not `$var`
- Use `$(command)` not backticks

## Argument Parsing

Use `while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do case $1 in ...` pattern (see existing scripts).
Always include a `--help` / `-h` option.

## Library Functions

Shared utilities go in `pipeline/lib/`:
- `prd-parser.sh` — parse PRD metadata (repos, status, title, priority)
- `progress.sh` — progress file read/write (`get_agent_status`, `is_agent_completed`)
- `git-utils.sh` — branch management and PR creation
- `validation.sh` — environment and PRD validation

Source them with: `source "$SCRIPT_DIR/lib/<file>.sh"`

## Testing Changes

```bash
# Single agent test (no PR)
./pipeline/run-agent.sh --agent architect --workdir /tmp/test-repo --prd ./templates/examples/sample-prd.md --max-iterations 2

# Single PRD × repo test (no PR)
./pipeline/run-pipeline.sh --prd ./templates/examples/sample-prd.md --repo <test-repo-url> --skip-pr

# Batch test (no PR)
./pipeline/orchestrator.sh --prd-dir ./templates/examples/ --skip-pr
```
